.Dd April 21, 2026
.Dt CLOWN-PLUGIN-PROTOCOL 7
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm clown-plugin-protocol
.Nd HTTP MCP server lifecycle protocol for clown plugins
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The clown plugin protocol enables Claude Code plugins to declare HTTP-based
MCP servers as local commands that are automatically launched at session
start and torn down at session end.
.Pp
HTTP MCP transports
.Pq Li streamable-http , Li sse
enable features unavailable over stdio:
.Bl -bullet -offset indent
.It
.Li notifications/tools/list_changed
\(em the server can push tool list updates to the client without polling
.It
Server-initiated requests via persistent SSE connections
.El
.Pp
The protocol covers four phases: discovery, handshake, health checking, and
shutdown.
It is modeled on the
.Lk https://github.com/hashicorp/go-plugin "hashicorp/go-plugin"
handshake protocol.
.Sh DISCOVERY
.Xr clown-plugin-host 1
receives plugin directories via
.Fl -plugin-dir
flags.
For each directory, it checks for a
.Pa clown.json
manifest (see
.Xr clown-json 5 ) .
Directories without
.Pa clown.json
are silently skipped.
.Pp
If no
.Pa clown.json
files are found in any plugin directory,
.Xr clown-plugin-host 1
exec's directly into the downstream command with zero overhead \(em no
child process, no intermediate config file.
.Pp
Each entry in
.Fa httpServers
within a discovered
.Pa clown.json
becomes a managed server.
The plugin name is read from
.Pa .claude-plugin/plugin.json
in the same directory.
.Sh HANDSHAKE PROTOCOL
Each HTTP MCP server MUST print a single pipe-delimited line to stdout
before serving requests:
.Pp
.Dl 1|1|tcp|127.0.0.1:54321|streamable-http
.Pp
.Ss Fields
.Bl -column "Pos" "Name" "Values" -offset indent
.It Sy Pos Ta Sy Name Ta Sy Values
.It 0 Ta Core protocol version Ta MUST be Li 1
.It 1 Ta App protocol version Ta Integer; MUST be Li 1 No (reserved)
.It 2 Ta Network type Ta MUST be Li tcp
.It 3 Ta Network address Ta Ar host Ns Li \&: Ns Ar port
.It 4 Ta Protocol Ta Li streamable-http No or Li sse
.El
.Ss Requirements
.Bl -bullet -offset indent
.It
The server MUST bind to
.Li 127.0.0.1:0
(ephemeral port, loopback only).
.It
The server MUST print the handshake line to stdout and flush.
.It
The server MUST begin serving HTTP requests after the handshake.
.It
The server MUST NOT write additional data to stdout after the handshake.
Diagnostic output MUST go to stderr.
.It
Extra fields beyond position 4 MAY be present and MUST be ignored by the
host.
.It
Leading and trailing whitespace MUST be tolerated by the parser.
.El
.Ss Protocol Authority
The protocol field in the handshake line is authoritative.
If it differs from the
.Fa transport
field in
.Pa clown.json ,
the handshake value takes precedence.
This allows servers to negotiate transport at runtime.
.Sh HEALTH CHECKING
After reading the handshake, the host polls
.Li http://<addr><healthcheck.path>
at the configured interval.
The server is considered healthy when it returns HTTP 200.
.Pp
Default health check parameters (overridable in
.Pa clown.json ) :
.Bl -tag -width Ds -offset indent
.It path
.Pa /healthz
.It interval
.Li 1s
.It timeout
.Li 30s
.El
.Pp
If the timeout elapses before a 200 response, the server process is
killed and an error is reported.
All servers are launched and health-checked in parallel.
If any server fails, all successfully started servers are shut down.
.Sh MCP CONFIGURATION
Once all servers are healthy, the host generates a temporary MCP
configuration file:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "<plugin-name>/<server-name>": {
      "url": "http://127.0.0.1:<port>/mcp"
    }
  }
}
.Ed
.Pp
Server names use the format
.Ar plugin-name Ns / Ns Ar server-name .
The URL path is
.Pa /mcp
for
.Li streamable-http
servers and
.Pa /sse
for
.Li sse
servers.
.Pp
The file is passed to the downstream command
.Pq typically Xr claude-code 1
via
.Fl -mcp-config .
.Sh SHUTDOWN
When the downstream command exits:
.Bl -enum -offset indent
.It
.Dv SIGTERM
is sent to each server's process group.
.It
The host waits up to 5 seconds for each server to exit gracefully.
.It
If a server has not exited after the grace period,
.Dv SIGKILL
is sent to its process group.
.It
The temporary MCP configuration file is removed.
.It
The host exits with the downstream command's exit code.
.El
.Sh PROCESS ISOLATION
Each server runs in its own process group
.Pq via Dv setpgid .
This provides:
.Bl -bullet -offset indent
.It
Clean signal delivery \(em the entire server process tree receives
.Dv SIGTERM .
.It
Reliable cleanup \(em
.Dv SIGKILL
reaches all child processes.
.It
Isolation between servers \(em one server's crash does not affect others.
.El
.Pp
The server's stderr is forwarded to the host's stderr with a
.Li [plugin-name/server-name]
prefix.
.Sh SECURITY CONSIDERATIONS
.Bl -bullet -offset indent
.It
Servers MUST bind to
.Li 127.0.0.1
only.
The protocol does not support remote addresses.
.It
Servers inherit the same trust level as any other code in the plugin \(em
they can read files, make network requests, and serve MCP tools that
influence model behavior.
.It
Clown's managed-settings guardrails (Bash disabled, auto-mode disabled)
apply regardless of which HTTP MCP servers are running.
Servers cannot override managed settings.
.El
.Sh ARCHITECTURE
.Bd -literal -offset indent
clown (shell wrapper)
  \(da exec clown-plugin-host --plugin-dir A -- claude [args]
       \(br\(em [no clown.json] \(-> exec claude directly
       \(da\(em [clown.json found]
            \(br\(em launch HTTP server children
            \(br\(em read handshake + poll healthz
            \(br\(em generate temp .mcp.json
            \(br\(em run claude as child with --mcp-config
            \(br\(em forward signals (SIGTERM, SIGINT)
            \(br\(em wait for claude to exit
            \(br\(em SIGTERM servers \(-> grace period \(-> SIGKILL
            \(da\(em exit with claude's exit code
.Ed
.Sh COMPATIBILITY
This protocol is additive.
Plugins without
.Pa clown.json
are unaffected (exec pass-through).
Existing stdio MCP servers in
.Pa .mcp.json
continue to work.
A plugin MAY ship both
.Pa clown.json
(for HTTP servers) and
.Pa .mcp.json
(for stdio servers) simultaneously.
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr clown-plugin-host 1 ,
.Xr clown-json 5 ,
.Xr clown 1 ,
.Xr claude-code 1
.Sh STANDARDS
This protocol is specified in full in
.Pa docs/rfcs/0002-clown-plugin-protocol.md
within the clown source repository.
.Pp
The handshake format is adapted from
.Lk https://github.com/hashicorp/go-plugin "hashicorp/go-plugin" .
